        "Keywords": "",
        "Description": "A heat pump is a device that transfers heat from a colder area to a hotter area by using mechanical energy, as in a refrigerator. Heat pumps are designed to move thermal energy opposite to the direction of spontaneous heat flow by absorbing heat from a cold space and releasing it to a warmer one. In this model, the heat pump is represented by its Coefficient of Performance (COP), which is calculated based on the Carnot efficiency and an assumed second law efficiency. The model also includes calculations for the power consumption of the heat pump and its specific investment cost, taking into account economic factors such as interest rate and lifetime.",
